abstract: A Times investigation showed how oligarchs and political patrons make millions in farm subsidies. But the program is all but sacrosanct.
snippet: A Times investigation showed how oligarchs and political patrons make millions in farm subsidies. But the program is all but sacrosanct.
lead_paragraph: BRUSSELS — European Union lawmakers on Tuesday strongly criticized corruption and self-dealing in the bloc’s $65-billion-a-year farm subsidy program but were sharply divided over how or whether to reform a system that has become a third rail of European politics.

abstract: The government is banking that anger at the strikers for making life miserable will tip the scales of public opinion in its favor. So far that is not happening.
snippet: The government is banking that anger at the strikers for making life miserable will tip the scales of public opinion in its favor. So far that is not happening.
lead_paragraph: PARIS — It was 5:50 in the afternoon in the Charles de Gaulle station on the RER A, the train that penetrates the suburbs of Paris. The crowd was already five deep. Only a narrow passageway remained on the platform.

abstract: In a rare public order, the secretive Foreign Intelligence Surveillance Court responded to problems with the eavesdropping on a former Trump campaign aide uncovered by an inspector general.
snippet: In a rare public order, the secretive Foreign Intelligence Surveillance Court responded to problems with the eavesdropping on a former Trump campaign aide uncovered by an inspector general.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A secretive federal court accused the F.B.I. on Tuesday of misleading judges about the rationale for wiretapping a former Trump campaign adviser and ordered the bureau to propose changes in how investigators seek their permission for national security surveillance targeting Americans.

abstract: The U.S. Congress on Tuesday approved the largest overhaul to the American military’s housing program in more than two decades, vowing to end slum-like living conditions and hold private landlords and defense officials accountable for them.
snippet: The U.S. Congress on Tuesday approved the largest overhaul to the American military’s housing program in more than two decades, vowing to end slum-like living conditions and hold private landlords and defense officials accountable for them.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - The U.S. Congress on Tuesday approved the largest overhaul to the American military’s housing program in more than two decades, vowing to end slum-like living conditions and hold private landlords and defense officials accountable for them.
headline_main: U.S. Congress Approves Sweeping Military Housing Overhaul
headline_print_headline: U.S. Congress Approves Sweeping Military Housing Overhaul

abstract: The Senate's top Democrat Chuck Schumer on Tuesday accused Mitch McConnell, the Senate's top Republican, of wanting to use the institution to help participate in a "cover-up" as the Senate prepares for a likely impeachment trial against U.S. President Donald Trump.
snippet: The Senate's top Democrat Chuck Schumer on Tuesday accused Mitch McConnell, the Senate's top Republican, of wanting to use the institution to help participate in a "cover-up" as the Senate prepares for a likely impeachment trial against U.S. Presi...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Senate's top Democrat Chuck Schumer on Tuesday accused Mitch McConnell, the Senate's top Republican, of wanting to use the institution to help participate in a "cover-up" as the Senate prepares for a likely impeachment trial against U.S. President Donald Trump.
headline_main: Schumer Accuses McConnell of Wanting to Use Senate for 'Cover-Up'
headline_print_headline: Schumer Accuses McConnell of Wanting to Use Senate for 'Cover-Up'

abstract: After a consequential but strangely inconclusive election, the prime minister still has not said what he means by Brexit.
snippet: After a consequential but strangely inconclusive election, the prime minister still has not said what he means by Brexit.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — Five days after British voters handed Prime Minister Boris Johnson the greatest political mandate of any Conservative leader since Margaret Thatcher, the country is still arguing over what he’s going to do with that power.

abstract: President Trump sent a letter on Tuesday to Speaker Nancy Pelosi expressing his “most powerful protest” against the impeachment process. The House is expected to vote on two articles of impeachment against Mr. Trump on Wednesday.
